1
00:00:05,606 --> 00:00:07,341
[Natsuki Takemiya]

2
00:00:07,341 --> 00:00:08,384
Huh?

3
00:00:11,445 --> 00:00:12,812
What did you just say?

4
00:00:14,114 --> 00:00:15,656
Let's break up.

5
00:00:17,760 --> 00:00:18,916
Why?

6
00:00:19,720 --> 00:00:20,921
[Natsuki's girlfriend, Sakura Nagai]

7
00:00:20,921 --> 00:00:24,700
Because Natsuki, you don't really love me.

8
00:00:24,700 --> 00:00:26,696
I do love you, Sakura.

9
00:00:29,730 --> 00:00:32,576
You said this summer we'd go to the beach,
see fireworks, go to festivals...

10
00:00:32,576 --> 00:00:35,816
Natsuki, you don't need me to be with you
to do all those things.

11
00:00:37,304 --> 00:00:38,952
- That's not true.
- Bye.

12
00:00:42,376 --> 00:00:43,592
Wait!

13
00:00:46,848 --> 00:00:48,036
I'm sorry.

14
00:00:53,120 --> 00:00:55,072
<i>Just before summer break</i>,

15
00:00:55,072 --> 00:00:57,968
<i>I got dumped by my girlfriend
of three months.</i>

16
00:01:06,300 --> 00:01:07,492
Why?

17
00:01:08,435 --> 00:01:11,271
[MULTI MART]

18
00:01:21,081 --> 00:01:24,118
[Refreshing Choco Mint]

19
00:01:24,118 --> 00:01:25,316
- Here you go.
- Huh?

20
00:01:26,592 --> 00:01:29,060
You're getting the usual, right, Natsuki?

21
00:01:29,060 --> 00:01:30,758
Yeah. Thanks!

22
00:01:30,758 --> 00:01:32,740
You're so consistent.

23
00:01:32,740 --> 00:01:34,316
I'm having this.

24
00:01:40,800 --> 00:01:42,148
Natsuki!

25
00:01:43,020 --> 00:01:44,260
[Neighboring kindergartener, Riku Yanagi]

26
00:01:44,260 --> 00:01:45,380
Riku?

27
00:01:45,380 --> 00:01:47,207
Aren't you getting me ice cream?

28
00:01:47,207 --> 00:01:48,776
Welcome!

29
00:01:48,776 --> 00:01:50,848
- Why?
- You're crying.

30
00:01:52,546 --> 00:01:54,208
No way! I wouldn't cry
over something like that.

31
00:01:54,208 --> 00:01:55,816
Then why are you crying?

32
00:01:58,852 --> 00:02:01,152
There are lots of things
you have to deal with as an adult.

33
00:02:01,152 --> 00:02:04,736
Huh? Why? Why were you crying?

34
00:02:06,496 --> 00:02:07,961
I got dumped.

35
00:02:07,961 --> 00:02:09,630
What does "dumped" mean?

36
00:02:09,630 --> 00:02:11,065
You'll understand someday.

37
00:02:11,065 --> 00:02:12,766
I want to know now.

38
00:02:12,766 --> 00:02:15,102
- It doesn't have to be now.
- Why not?

39
00:02:15,102 --> 00:02:17,771
Hey, why not? Why not, why not?

40
00:02:17,771 --> 00:02:19,840
"Getting dumped" means,

41
00:02:19,840 --> 00:02:22,876
being told by someone you like
that they don't like you.

42
00:02:22,876 --> 00:02:24,132
Huh?

43
00:02:33,153 --> 00:02:36,457
Is that so? You sound like a teacher!

44
00:02:36,457 --> 00:02:37,600
Really?

45
00:02:40,540 --> 00:02:42,820
Cheer up, Natsuki.

46
00:02:44,398 --> 00:02:48,928
Riku, what we talked about just now,
don't tell Grandpa.

47
00:02:48,928 --> 00:02:52,768
Got it! Bye-bye.

48
00:02:53,504 --> 00:02:55,676
Grandpa!

49
00:02:55,676 --> 00:02:58,945
[Former musician, Eiichi Yanagi]

50
00:03:00,768 --> 00:03:03,524
Did I say too much?

51
00:03:04,651 --> 00:03:06,053
Not really.

52
00:03:06,053 --> 00:03:07,254
I'm sorry.

53
00:03:07,254 --> 00:03:10,416
It's just that the "why, why" questions
seemed endless.

54
00:03:10,416 --> 00:03:12,260
You could at least say that in a proper way.

55
00:03:12,260 --> 00:03:14,376
Anyway, try to cheer up.

56
00:03:23,904 --> 00:03:26,039
I can't stand this.

57
00:03:26,039 --> 00:03:28,776
I heard that Natsuki got dumped.

58
00:03:28,776 --> 00:03:30,978
I told you not to tell!

59
00:03:30,978 --> 00:03:32,446
Natsuki.

60
00:03:32,446 --> 00:03:33,647
Yes?

61
00:03:33,647 --> 00:03:36,128
[Nothing is permanent!]
Nothing is permanent!

62
00:03:36,128 --> 00:03:37,184
Huh?

63
00:03:37,184 --> 00:03:40,800
Everything is always in flux. Good luck!

64
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:42,024
Good luck!

65
00:03:55,002 --> 00:03:57,984
[Episode 1]

66
00:04:07,584 --> 00:04:11,418
Everything is always in flux.

67
00:04:11,418 --> 00:04:12,448
[Everything is always in flux]

68
00:04:12,448 --> 00:04:15,624
I guess nothing lasts forever, does it?

69
00:04:24,832 --> 00:04:27,067
Did you come to comfort me?

70
00:04:27,067 --> 00:04:28,672
[Takemiya family's dog, Rock]
You're so kind, Rock.

71
00:04:28,672 --> 00:04:30,492
Sorry to keep you waiting,

72
00:04:30,492 --> 00:04:32,320
[Natsuki's mother, Towako Takemiya]
I forgot the recipe.

73
00:04:32,320 --> 00:04:34,341
- I left it behind.
- Okay.

74
00:04:34,341 --> 00:04:38,208
- Towako, is this okay?
- Let me see.

75
00:04:38,208 --> 00:04:40,214
- With this?
- Did you add a little of this?

76
00:04:40,214 --> 00:04:43,168
Towako, we're out of olive oil.

77
00:04:43,168 --> 00:04:44,672
Huh? Oh.

78
00:04:46,320 --> 00:04:47,808
Yes?

79
00:04:47,808 --> 00:04:48,928
Please wait a moment.

80
00:04:48,928 --> 00:04:49,952
- Yes.
- Got it.

81
00:04:50,824 --> 00:04:52,000
Okay.

82
00:04:57,568 --> 00:04:58,632
[Cooking class student, Mayumi Tachibana]

83
00:04:58,632 --> 00:05:00,934
Natsuki seems a bit down.

84
00:05:00,934 --> 00:05:02,336
I wonder what's wrong?

85
00:05:02,336 --> 00:05:03,552
[Cooking class student, Kaoru Kimijima]

86
00:05:03,552 --> 00:05:05,472
- Excuse me.
- Hi.

87
00:05:09,476 --> 00:05:12,746
Natsuki... I heard he got dumped.

88
00:05:12,746 --> 00:05:13,824
- What?
- What?

89
00:05:14,982 --> 00:05:16,416
Why did you have to say that?

90
00:05:16,416 --> 00:05:18,080
- He got dumped?
- Natsuki?

91
00:05:18,080 --> 00:05:19,219
By Sakura?

92
00:05:19,219 --> 00:05:21,504
I don't know her name.

93
00:05:21,504 --> 00:05:23,460
Wasn't she the soccer team's manager?

94
00:05:23,460 --> 00:05:26,112
Yes, that's right. She lives
in the same apartment as Mr. Gotou.

95
00:05:26,112 --> 00:05:27,928
Oh, the one on 2nd Street.

96
00:05:27,928 --> 00:05:31,765
Excuse me, I can hear you guys
loud and clear here.

97
00:05:31,765 --> 00:05:33,267
Sorry.

98
00:05:33,267 --> 00:05:36,370
Well, it's because
you don't say anything, Natsuki.

99
00:05:36,370 --> 00:05:38,368
You wouldn't report this
to my parents, right?

100
00:05:40,512 --> 00:05:43,210
It's okay, Natsuki. You don't have to worry.

101
00:05:43,210 --> 00:05:46,048
That's right, heartbreak is something
that everyone goes through.

102
00:05:46,048 --> 00:05:49,216
We've been through it so many times.

103
00:05:49,216 --> 00:05:50,851
I haven't, though.

104
00:05:50,851 --> 00:05:51,872
Really? Is that so?

105
00:05:51,872 --> 00:05:55,232
You'll find someone better, Natsuki.

106
00:05:55,232 --> 00:05:58,058
That's right. There are lots of people who'd
be happy to know that you're single, Natsuki.

107
00:05:58,058 --> 00:05:59,860
There are plenty.

108
00:05:59,860 --> 00:06:01,828
- You think so?
- Yes, absolutely.

109
00:06:01,828 --> 00:06:04,677
- They're already posting about it over there.
- No way!

110
00:06:04,677 --> 00:06:07,808
- Going for a love hat-trick, maybe?
- Come on.

111
00:06:07,808 --> 00:06:11,038
Mayumi, Kaoru,
you're both so sweet with Natsuki.

112
00:06:11,038 --> 00:06:15,640
- That's because we're Natsuki's fandom, right?
- Right?

113
00:06:15,640 --> 00:06:17,044
What's a fandom?

114
00:06:17,044 --> 00:06:19,179
It means a group of fans.

115
00:06:19,179 --> 00:06:20,447
I see.

116
00:06:20,447 --> 00:06:23,183
I used to have one too.

117
00:06:23,183 --> 00:06:25,300
Well, can I ask you something?

118
00:06:25,300 --> 00:06:26,853
What is it?

119
00:06:26,853 --> 00:06:28,388
My...

120
00:06:28,388 --> 00:06:30,390
- What are my good qualities?
- Your looks.

121
00:06:30,390 --> 00:06:31,776
- Great body.
- Yeah.

122
00:06:31,776 --> 00:06:34,024
Thanks, but that's too much praise.

123
00:06:35,295 --> 00:06:37,531
What about personality-wise?

124
00:06:37,531 --> 00:06:40,000
You're kind. Friendly.

125
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:41,234
A pure boy.

126
00:06:41,234 --> 00:06:43,456
Do you mean that I have
an unpretentious personality?

127
00:06:43,456 --> 00:06:46,840
- Yeah, exactly.
- You're saying it yourself.

128
00:06:46,840 --> 00:06:48,175
I'm home.

129
00:06:48,175 --> 00:06:50,210
Welcome back.

130
00:06:50,210 --> 00:06:52,576
The noisy one is back.

131
00:06:52,576 --> 00:06:54,320
[Natsuki's sister, Riyo Takemiya]
- I'm home. - Welcome back.

132
00:06:54,320 --> 00:06:56,550
- Welcome back.
- Welcome back.

133
00:06:56,550 --> 00:06:57,832
Come on, come on in.

134
00:07:05,759 --> 00:07:06,944
Excuse me for intruding.

135
00:07:10,564 --> 00:07:12,065
[Riyo's boyfriend, Souta Kobayakawa]
This is Souta Kobayakawa.

136
00:07:12,065 --> 00:07:13,700
My boyfriend.

137
00:07:13,700 --> 00:07:16,328
- Welcome.
- Nice to meet you.

138
00:07:19,406 --> 00:07:21,504
Oh, thanks for earlier.

139
00:07:21,504 --> 00:07:23,876
- What? Does everyone know each other?
- No!

140
00:07:24,578 --> 00:07:26,284
We ran into each other
at the convenience store earlier.

141
00:07:28,832 --> 00:07:30,304
So could it be...

142
00:07:30,944 --> 00:07:33,080
The high schooler crying
at the convenience store

143
00:07:33,080 --> 00:07:35,208
- was Natsuki?
- Yes, exactly.

144
00:07:37,658 --> 00:07:39,600
- Hang on a sec.
- Okay.

145
00:07:41,294 --> 00:07:44,224
So, Towako, what shall we do today?

146
00:07:44,224 --> 00:07:47,200
Oh, Mr. Yanagi,
aren't you enthusiastic today?

147
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:48,924
Thanks.

148
00:07:48,924 --> 00:07:51,405
- So your name is Souta?
- Yes.

149
00:07:51,405 --> 00:07:53,974
How did you get acquainted with Riyo?
A dating app?

150
00:07:53,974 --> 00:07:55,642
No, we go to the same university.

151
00:07:55,642 --> 00:07:57,664
Is that so? You're so talented.

152
00:07:57,664 --> 00:07:59,112
Thank you.

153
00:07:59,112 --> 00:08:01,460
He really is such an unlikable guy.

154
00:08:02,716 --> 00:08:04,320
I knew you'd get dumped.

155
00:08:04,320 --> 00:08:06,687
It was really only a matter of time.

156
00:08:06,687 --> 00:08:07,988
Why?

157
00:08:07,988 --> 00:08:10,123
Because you're so insensitive, Natsuki.

158
00:08:10,123 --> 00:08:12,125
No, I'm actually quite sensitive.

159
00:08:12,125 --> 00:08:15,062
People who are actually sensitive
don't say things like that.

160
00:08:15,062 --> 00:08:17,631
- That's not true.
- See? You don't understand.

161
00:08:17,631 --> 00:08:21,344
- Huh?
- You're nowhere near ready for romance.

162
00:08:21,344 --> 00:08:23,704
- I don't want to hear that coming from you.
- Why not?

163
00:08:23,704 --> 00:08:25,824
Because your relationships never last long.

164
00:08:25,824 --> 00:08:26,973
What? Are you picking a fight?

165
00:08:26,973 --> 00:08:28,672
You started it, didn't you?

166
00:08:28,672 --> 00:08:30,977
- Look...
- Will everything be okay with them?

167
00:08:30,977 --> 00:08:32,813
No need to worry.

168
00:08:32,813 --> 00:08:34,464
It's always like this.

169
00:08:34,464 --> 00:08:35,588
Right?

170
00:08:37,584 --> 00:08:39,108
Is that so?

171
00:08:40,187 --> 00:08:41,540
Unbelievable.

172
00:08:41,540 --> 00:08:43,680
That's why you're like this.

173
00:08:45,992 --> 00:08:47,561
Sorry, Rock.

174
00:08:47,561 --> 00:08:50,136
We're not fighting.

175
00:08:50,136 --> 00:08:51,432
Sorry.

176
00:08:52,432 --> 00:08:57,696
You know, whenever someone's fighting,
Rock always steps in to mediate.

177
00:09:01,241 --> 00:09:02,409
That's impressive.

178
00:09:02,409 --> 00:09:05,078
- Do you want to go for a walk?
- Want to go for a walk with me?

179
00:09:07,748 --> 00:09:09,088
Aren't you hot, Rock?

180
00:09:11,785 --> 00:09:12,886
I see.

181
00:09:12,886 --> 00:09:14,454
That's good.

182
00:09:18,624 --> 00:09:20,160
I want to go to the beach.

183
00:09:31,744 --> 00:09:33,888
I got dumped.

184
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:46,900
Let's go, Rock!

185
00:09:56,544 --> 00:09:57,984
I'm home.

186
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:01,200
Natsuki, come here for a moment.

187
00:10:02,500 --> 00:10:04,200
Did I do something wrong?

188
00:10:13,300 --> 00:10:15,000
Well...

189
00:10:16,768 --> 00:10:19,712
[Senior Year National College Choice Exam
(2nd Round) Individual Score Report]

190
00:10:19,712 --> 00:10:21,312
Why is it here?

191
00:10:21,312 --> 00:10:24,608
You said the mock exam results
weren't out yet, didn't you?

192
00:10:24,608 --> 00:10:26,336
Well...

193
00:10:27,008 --> 00:10:29,376
[Natsuki and Riyo's father, Gorou Takemiya]
I've never seen an E rating before.

194
00:10:29,376 --> 00:10:31,360
Right? It's surprising.

195
00:10:31,360 --> 00:10:32,928
But why is it here?

196
00:10:32,928 --> 00:10:35,424
I went into your room
thinking I'd borrow a T-shirt,

197
00:10:35,424 --> 00:10:37,056
and found that in the trash bin.

198
00:10:37,056 --> 00:10:38,112
You shouldn't just pick it up.

199
00:10:38,112 --> 00:10:41,024
Hiding it because
you thought you'd get scolded.

200
00:10:41,024 --> 00:10:43,059
It's like you haven't matured at all
since elementary school.

201
00:10:43,059 --> 00:10:45,083
You used to do that a lot.

202
00:10:45,083 --> 00:10:47,163
You thought you'd hidden it well,
but actually, you hadn't.

203
00:10:47,163 --> 00:10:50,300
- Rock's shocked too.
- No, that's not true.

204
00:10:50,300 --> 00:10:52,300
You're on my side, right, Rock?

205
00:10:53,803 --> 00:10:56,773
You scored 12 points on math.

206
00:10:56,773 --> 00:10:58,947
Seriously, how did you manage
to get a score like that?

207
00:10:58,947 --> 00:11:00,991
I really wonder.

208
00:11:00,991 --> 00:11:04,571
Natsuki, are you planning
to take the entrance exam?

209
00:11:04,571 --> 00:11:07,684
Yes, I want to take it.
I want to go to college.

210
00:11:07,684 --> 00:11:10,020
- Which school?
- Which department?

211
00:11:10,020 --> 00:11:12,100
I'm still thinking about it.

212
00:11:13,223 --> 00:11:15,559
Well, there's still time.

213
00:11:15,559 --> 00:11:16,983
That's unacceptable!

214
00:11:16,983 --> 00:11:19,331
It's already July.

215
00:11:19,331 --> 00:11:22,895
Just so you know,
college entrance exams aren't that easy.

216
00:11:23,900 --> 00:11:26,300
I can do it if I try.

217
00:11:26,303 --> 00:11:30,574
That's true. You're amazing
when you're focused, Natsuki.

218
00:11:30,574 --> 00:11:32,023
Right?

219
00:11:32,023 --> 00:11:34,523
But it doesn't last.

220
00:11:34,523 --> 00:11:37,795
You quickly become
engrossed in chatting with Rock.

221
00:11:39,082 --> 00:11:43,186
Riyo, why don't you teach him math?

222
00:11:43,200 --> 00:11:44,600
- Absolutely not!
- No way!

223
00:11:45,363 --> 00:11:47,891
Because she'll throw an eraser
the moment I don't understand something.

224
00:11:47,891 --> 00:11:50,260
Because you immediately give up
when you don't understand something.

225
00:11:50,260 --> 00:11:51,494
Your teaching methods are terrible.

226
00:11:51,494 --> 00:11:53,330
Maybe it's just because you are stupid.

227
00:11:53,330 --> 00:11:54,764
- I'm not stupid!
- Huh?

228
00:11:54,800 --> 00:11:58,700
Anyway, Natsuki,

229
00:11:58,700 --> 00:12:01,871
if you get an E rating on the next mock exam,

230
00:12:01,871 --> 00:12:04,003
you can just give up on
the college entrance exam.

231
00:12:04,003 --> 00:12:05,027
Huh?

232
00:12:05,809 --> 00:12:07,243
Right.

233
00:12:07,243 --> 00:12:08,419
That's right.

234
00:12:11,648 --> 00:12:12,939
I'll do my best.

235
00:12:27,697 --> 00:12:29,312
[Sakura: Yeah]

236
00:12:31,701 --> 00:12:35,672
Natsuki has difficulty getting focused.

237
00:12:35,672 --> 00:12:40,777
Maybe it's because he doesn't have
a clear goal for college, right?

238
00:12:40,777 --> 00:12:44,291
Wanting to become
an aircraft engineer like you did,

239
00:12:44,291 --> 00:12:49,219
I don't think many people
get into school with a clear goal like that.

240
00:12:49,219 --> 00:12:52,515
But even Riyo, she chose to study languages.

241
00:12:53,156 --> 00:12:54,791
That's true.

242
00:12:54,791 --> 00:12:58,887
Wanting to travel the world
is also a valid goal.

243
00:12:59,683 --> 00:13:01,798
Unlike the two of you,

244
00:13:01,798 --> 00:13:04,835
I just wanted to leave the countryside,
so I went to a junior college.

245
00:13:05,769 --> 00:13:06,903
I see.

246
00:13:06,903 --> 00:13:10,974
So I can relate to Natsuki's feelings.

247
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:14,600
I have a feeling that he'll find something
if he goes to college.

248
00:13:15,578 --> 00:13:17,095
Something...

249
00:13:20,864 --> 00:13:22,179
[Math Workbook]

250
00:13:22,179 --> 00:13:23,299
Nice job.

251
00:13:29,987 --> 00:13:31,011
Who could that be?

252
00:13:33,315 --> 00:13:34,371
[Takemiya]
Huh?

253
00:13:36,355 --> 00:13:37,443
Hi.

254
00:13:40,336 --> 00:13:42,403
But my sister isn't home.

255
00:13:43,500 --> 00:13:45,100
Yeah, I know.

256
00:13:45,100 --> 00:13:48,291
Then, did she forget something?

257
00:13:50,547 --> 00:13:52,482
I've been asked to tutor.

258
00:13:52,482 --> 00:13:55,235
Tutor? Tutor whom?

259
00:13:58,179 --> 00:13:59,203
Me?

260
00:13:59,923 --> 00:14:01,191
What?

261
00:14:01,191 --> 00:14:03,660
Why did you just arrange that
without asking me?

262
00:14:03,660 --> 00:14:06,403
<i>Since Souta is good at math and science,
I thought he'd be a perfect tutor.</i>

263
00:14:08,323 --> 00:14:12,163
I find him a bit uncomfortable to be around,
and really unlikable.

264
00:14:12,902 --> 00:14:14,704
Really unlikable?

265
00:14:14,704 --> 00:14:17,073
That's funny. You've been reading
those Yankee comics, haven't you?

266
00:14:17,073 --> 00:14:18,975
They're pretty popular
among people my age right now.

267
00:14:18,975 --> 00:14:21,678
But don't worry,
even if you think he's unlikable now,

268
00:14:21,678 --> 00:14:23,747
the more you get to know him,
the more you'll like him.

269
00:14:23,747 --> 00:14:25,123
I don't need to like him.

270
00:14:25,123 --> 00:14:28,852
Souta has tutoring experience,
and he's kind, so his teaching style is good.

271
00:14:28,852 --> 00:14:30,659
I can't handle one-on-one lessons.

272
00:14:31,688 --> 00:14:34,823
Natsuki, are you really okay
with how things are now?

273
00:14:36,359 --> 00:14:38,128
<i>If you go to university,</i>

274
00:14:38,128 --> 00:14:40,643
<i>I don't think your life
will definitely change,</i>

275
00:14:41,543 --> 00:14:43,815
but university could still be a catalyst
for some kind of change.

276
00:14:47,303 --> 00:14:48,867
That's true.

277
00:14:50,203 --> 00:14:51,808
Oh, over here, over here!

278
00:14:51,808 --> 00:14:53,376
Good job.

279
00:14:53,376 --> 00:14:55,811
Make sure you do your best
to learn from Souta.

280
00:14:55,811 --> 00:14:58,503
If you try to skip out,
I'll break your phone.

281
00:15:10,226 --> 00:15:12,662
Are you not very good with dogs?

282
00:15:12,662 --> 00:15:14,499
No, not at all.

283
00:15:15,555 --> 00:15:18,368
Seems like he's afraid of you, Rock.

284
00:15:18,368 --> 00:15:20,036
Even though you're such a good boy.

285
00:15:20,036 --> 00:15:21,867
- I'm not scared...
- Go, Rock!

286
00:15:24,474 --> 00:15:25,639
See? You are scared.

287
00:15:26,467 --> 00:15:29,795
No, I was just surprised.

288
00:15:31,614 --> 00:15:33,739
All right, Rock, that's enough for now.

289
00:15:38,388 --> 00:15:40,611
What did Riyo say?

290
00:15:41,791 --> 00:15:43,683
She said that if I skip our
tutoring sessions, she'd break my phone.

291
00:15:44,794 --> 00:15:46,475
She seems like someone
who might actually do that.

292
00:15:48,131 --> 00:15:51,623
So, let's just leave it at that for today.

293
00:15:53,837 --> 00:15:54,951
Let's do this!

294
00:16:02,412 --> 00:16:03,911
Where's your room, Natsuki?

295
00:16:04,611 --> 00:16:07,395
Well, right here!

296
00:16:08,551 --> 00:16:10,531
Please, right here.

297
00:16:14,691 --> 00:16:16,771
I'm not about to let someone
I don't know into my room.

298
00:16:24,800 --> 00:16:26,272
Just do what you can.

299
00:16:29,952 --> 00:16:31,472
Well...

300
00:16:35,168 --> 00:16:37,795
Or is it that you can't do any of this?

301
00:16:41,376 --> 00:16:42,791
I see.

302
00:16:44,352 --> 00:16:46,752
That means that this workbook
isn't suitable for you.

303
00:16:49,024 --> 00:16:50,435
Then...

304
00:16:56,000 --> 00:16:58,019
How about this?

305
00:17:01,184 --> 00:17:02,371
Give it a try.

306
00:17:14,848 --> 00:17:16,547
It's hard for me to work while being watched.

307
00:17:17,728 --> 00:17:19,232
Then let me know when you're done.

308
00:18:01,955 --> 00:18:03,011
All done.

309
00:18:04,131 --> 00:18:05,315
Let me see.

310
00:18:11,680 --> 00:18:13,952
Oh, so close.

311
00:18:13,952 --> 00:18:16,256
You had it right up until here.

312
00:18:16,256 --> 00:18:17,539
Seriously?

313
00:18:19,392 --> 00:18:24,448
If you do this here, like this,
you'll get the correct answer.

314
00:18:24,448 --> 00:18:26,080
I see.

315
00:18:26,080 --> 00:18:29,795
Nice. All right, next...

316
00:18:33,699 --> 00:18:34,755
Try this one.

317
00:18:40,896 --> 00:18:43,264
Okay, that's all for today.

318
00:18:44,064 --> 00:18:45,735
All done!

319
00:18:53,536 --> 00:18:54,816
You did well.

320
00:19:02,115 --> 00:19:03,839
Stop it.

321
00:19:03,839 --> 00:19:07,555
Sorry, it's just a habit of mine
from teaching elementary school kids.

322
00:19:08,608 --> 00:19:10,499
Don't lump me in with little kids!

323
00:19:12,547 --> 00:19:13,603
By the way...

324
00:19:15,488 --> 00:19:17,347
These are what I give to
elementary school students.

325
00:19:17,952 --> 00:19:19,203
[Great job]
Do you want one?

326
00:19:20,832 --> 00:19:22,464
Maybe.

327
00:19:22,464 --> 00:19:23,904
You want it.

328
00:19:23,904 --> 00:19:27,904
If I collect ten of these,
I get something, right?

329
00:19:27,904 --> 00:19:32,000
Oh... Yeah. I'll think of something.

330
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:34,496
- Here.
- Thanks.

331
00:19:41,531 --> 00:19:43,232
[Great job]

332
00:19:45,600 --> 00:19:47,619
What's your first-choice school, Natsuki?

333
00:19:49,152 --> 00:19:52,355
I haven't decided yet.
Just somewhere I can get in.

334
00:19:53,248 --> 00:19:54,819
<i>What's your first-choice school, Natsuki?</i>

335
00:19:55,872 --> 00:19:57,379
Somewhere I can get in.

336
00:19:58,816 --> 00:20:01,792
You're not saying the same university as me?

337
00:20:01,792 --> 00:20:04,739
No way. You're way smarter than me.

338
00:20:06,528 --> 00:20:07,747
I see.

339
00:20:09,864 --> 00:20:11,048
Natsuki?

340
00:20:11,971 --> 00:20:13,568
Huh?

341
00:20:13,568 --> 00:20:15,936
You don't have to have a first-choice school,

342
00:20:15,936 --> 00:20:19,072
but you do need some motivation
for your entrance exams.

343
00:20:19,072 --> 00:20:20,995
Something to keep pushing for.

344
00:20:21,699 --> 00:20:25,952
Motivation, huh? Like what?

345
00:20:25,952 --> 00:20:28,867
After you get into university,
the things you want to do.

346
00:20:32,992 --> 00:20:36,803
I always wrote them down on paper
and kept them where I could always see.

347
00:20:38,464 --> 00:20:40,739
It's kind of like a charm.

348
00:20:42,176 --> 00:20:43,395
A charm.

349
00:20:44,032 --> 00:20:48,192
Like eating a big steak if you pass,
or buying a pair of sneakers you want,

350
00:20:48,192 --> 00:20:51,203
or walking on campus with someone you like.

351
00:20:53,120 --> 00:20:55,744
You're not saying the same university as me?

352
00:20:55,744 --> 00:20:58,979
Natsuki, you don't really love me.

353
00:21:01,952 --> 00:21:06,784
Maybe, with someone you really like,

354
00:21:06,784 --> 00:21:09,536
you'd want to walk on campus together, right?

355
00:21:10,272 --> 00:21:12,163
Probably, right?

356
00:21:14,432 --> 00:21:17,571
Natsuki, you don't need me to be with you
to do all those things.

357
00:21:19,424 --> 00:21:20,899
I see.

358
00:21:23,296 --> 00:21:24,739
Natsuki?

359
00:21:28,739 --> 00:21:33,603
I really am insensitive and awful.

360
00:21:36,864 --> 00:21:38,947
I don't know what you mean,

361
00:21:39,712 --> 00:21:41,376
but you don't have to
put yourself down like that.

362
00:21:41,376 --> 00:21:42,563
Hey.

363
00:21:46,976 --> 00:21:49,792
How can you genuinely
fall in love with someone?

364
00:21:51,584 --> 00:21:52,960
Huh?

365
00:21:52,960 --> 00:21:55,424
That's a very philosophical question
all of a sudden.

366
00:21:55,424 --> 00:21:56,739
I want to know the answer.

367
00:21:58,464 --> 00:22:02,499
There's not just one right answer,
which makes it a difficult area.

368
00:22:04,224 --> 00:22:06,019
So there is no single answer.

369
00:22:08,416 --> 00:22:10,912
I think it might be different
for each person, you know?

370
00:22:13,219 --> 00:22:14,275
I see.

371
00:22:18,144 --> 00:22:19,363
I've decided!

372
00:22:20,640 --> 00:22:21,955
Something you want to do?

373
00:22:34,784 --> 00:22:37,472
This will be my good luck charm, okay?

374
00:22:37,472 --> 00:22:38,691
What did you write?

375
00:22:39,776 --> 00:22:41,600
[Genuinely falling in love]

376
00:22:41,600 --> 00:22:42,848
I'm not telling you.

377
00:22:42,848 --> 00:22:44,419
Come on.

378
00:22:47,328 --> 00:22:49,888
I'll tell you when it comes true.

379
00:22:53,056 --> 00:22:57,536
So, the tutoring,
we'll continue with it like this, right?

380
00:22:57,536 --> 00:22:59,296
Yeah, it's kind of like that.

381
00:22:59,904 --> 00:23:01,379
Please.

382
00:23:02,848 --> 00:23:04,227
All right!

383
00:23:14,400 --> 00:23:20,000
<i>Together in the summer,
love and storminess came to our home.</i>

